WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.359 --> 00:00:11.170
At the north end of Cascade, we will take
Highway 22, northeast to Warm Lake.

00:00:11.170 --> 00:00:16.340
And turn south to the 474 road,
very close to the South Fork Salmon River

00:00:16.340 --> 00:00:22.290
Campground; and follow the 474 road about
6 miles to our last stop the Stolle Meadows

00:00:22.290 --> 00:00:24.070
Cabin.

00:00:24.070 --> 00:00:29.820
The historic and rustic Stolle Meadows Cabin
is a single-room dwelling that has been restored

00:00:29.820 --> 00:00:31.430
to near original condition.

00:00:31.430 --> 00:00:37.829
It is located in a beautiful meadow near a
variety of recreational activities.

00:00:37.829 --> 00:00:45.120
The cabin is available year-round with a reservation
from www.recreation.gov.

00:00:45.120 --> 00:00:51.210
In winter, visitors ski and snowmobile the
6.5 miles to the cabin and in the summer months

00:00:51.210 --> 00:00:56.920
Warm Lake is less than 5 miles with plenty
of boating, fishing and swimming.

00:00:56.920 --> 00:01:03.410
The cabin contains four single beds with foam
pads, a table and chairs, dry sink, wood stove

00:01:03.410 --> 00:01:09.380
and firewood, propane cooking stove with fuel,
pots and pans, dishes and tableware.

00:01:09.380 --> 00:01:12.970
There is no electricity available at the cabin.

00:01:12.970 --> 00:01:17.440
There is an outhouse with vault toilet and
picnic table located outside.

00:01:17.440 --> 00:01:22.650
Drinking water is available year-round from
a hand pump outside the cabin.

00:01:22.650 --> 00:01:26.860
Pets are allowed at the cabin and guests are
asked to bring their own additional gear and

00:01:26.860 --> 00:01:31.170
supplies including bedding and extra lighting.

00:01:31.170 --> 00:01:34.030
